			{
				"type": "Comment",
				"start": 0,
				"end": 492,
				"data": " An empty block-body element inside <pre> that overflows. tsv indents one level shallower than prettier and preserves the source close form for both a component and an HTML inline element: self-closing keeps `/>`, explicit-empty keeps its close tag. When the attrs fit they stay on one line (only the close moves to its own line); when they are too long they wrap one per line — the `/>` still drops to its own line, never hugging the last attr. output_prettier shows prettier's form. "
			},
